snd-hda-codec-cs8409-imac (1.6) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Report the headphone jack as always present so PipeWire/WirePlumber keeps a
    usable output sink instead of falling back to Dummy Output. The reused
    CS42L42 detection mis-reads the iMac's inverted jack circuit; since the
    headphone is the only analog output, a fixed-present port is the pragmatic
    fix. Mic detection is left intact.

 -- Peter Shev <peter@shev.it>  Thu, 18 Jun 2026 16:45:00 +0000

snd-hda-codec-cs8409-imac (1.5) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Power up the CS42L83 headphone output stage at playback. The boot value of
    PWR_CTL1 (0x1101=0xfe) leaves HP/MIXER/ASP-in powered down; the playback
    hook now walks it 0xfe -> 0x9e -> 0x96 (ASP_DAI+MIXER on, wait power-good,
    then HP on), matching the macOS output enable. This was the silence cause.

 -- Peter Shev <peter@shev.it>  Thu, 18 Jun 2026 16:20:00 +0000

snd-hda-codec-cs8409-imac (1.4) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Re-run the CS42L83 bring-up in the playback PREPARE hook (clocks live) so
    the companion DAC's PLL locks, mirroring how macOS enables the DAC at
    playback start. Log STATUS/PLL/OSC at prepare to confirm the lock.

 -- Peter Shev <peter@shev.it>  Thu, 18 Jun 2026 15:55:00 +0000

snd-hda-codec-cs8409-imac (1.3) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Diagnostic build: log key CS42L83 state (power, codec status, HP_CTL mute,
    PLL, serial-clock source) after bring-up to isolate why the headphone path
    is silent despite a correctly configured CS8409 ASP2 transmit path.

 -- Peter Shev <peter@shev.it>  Thu, 18 Jun 2026 15:30:00 +0000

snd-hda-codec-cs8409-imac (1.2) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Fix the ASP2 headphone clocking: replace the Dell speaker clock-divider
    values (ASP2_CLK_CTRL1=0x801f, CTRL3=0x805c) with the Apple CS42L83 44.1kHz
    values (0x8000 / 0x0042) and restore the ASP2 TX-rate writes, faithfully
    matching the macOS setupTDMPath sequence. Wrong dividers produced silence.

 -- Peter Shev <peter@shev.it>  Thu, 18 Jun 2026 13:45:00 +0000

snd-hda-codec-cs8409-imac (1.1) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Route playback to the CS42L83 headphone path: force the internal-speaker
    pins (ASP1, 0x24/0x25) disabled so the parser uses the ASP2 headphone DAC
    instead of the unconfigured speaker DAC.
  * Add a CS42L83-specific suspend that avoids the CS42L42 PDN_DONE poll
    (eliminates the repeated "Timeout waiting for PDN_DONE" messages).

 -- Peter Shev <peter@shev.it>  Thu, 18 Jun 2026 11:30:00 +0000

snd-hda-codec-cs8409-imac (1.0) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Initial DKMS package.
  * Add Apple iMac18,3 (CS8409/CS42L83) support to the in-kernel CS8409 codec:
    - SND_PCI_QUIRK / model "imac18-3" for subsystem 0x106b1000.
    - CS42L83 44.1kHz multi-page I2C bring-up sequence.
    - CS8409 ASP2 headphone TDM path with 44.1kHz clocking.
    - GPIO mapping (GPIO1 reset, GPIO0 IRQ, GPIO4 amp enable).

 -- Peter Shev <peter@shev.it>  Thu, 18 Jun 2026 08:20:00 +0000
